  <!-- Roadworks Coordination Issue (Burnley-specific) -->
  <section class="chaos-section" data-region-only="burnley">
    <div class="container">
      <ScrollReveal>
        <div class="chaos-card">
          <div class="chaos-inner">
            <span class="chaos-label">February &ndash; March 2026</span>
            <h2>The Roadworks Coordination Problem</h2>
            <p>
              In early 2026, multiple major roadworks schemes hit Burnley simultaneously. The &pound;55M Levelling Up
              programme introduced a one-way system on Manchester Road. Colne Road had two-way signals for
              highway improvements. Hammerton Street was closed. Utility companies were digging on Accrington Road and Barden Lane.
            </p>
            <p>
              Burnley&rsquo;s MP described conditions as &ldquo;utterly unmanageable.&rdquo; Journeys normally
              taking 10 minutes were taking over an hour. Businesses reported lost footfall, inability to receive deliveries,
              and property damage from diverted HGV traffic.
            </p>
            <div class="chaos-roads">
              <span class="chaos-road">Manchester Road</span>
              <span class="chaos-road">Colne Road</span>
              <span class="chaos-road">Hammerton Street</span>
              <span class="chaos-road">Accrington Road</span>
              <span class="chaos-road">Barden Lane</span>
              <span class="chaos-road">Rossendale Road</span>
              <span class="chaos-road">Centenary Way</span>
            </div>
            <p class="chaos-note">
              The core issue: LCC controls the highways, but the Levelling Up programme is partly funded and managed
              by central government with Burnley Borough Council. Utility companies (Cadent Gas, United Utilities, Openreach)
              have statutory rights to dig up roads with limited council control over timing. Better coordination between
              all parties is essential.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </ScrollReveal>
    </div>
  </section>

