        <div class="safety-grid stagger-children">
          <div class="safety-card">
            <h3>Average Speed Cameras</h3>
            <span class="safety-location">Colne Road (new, 2026)</span>
            <p>
              Installed as part of the Colne Road highway improvements following stakeholder feedback.
              Average speed cameras measure speed over a distance rather than at a single point,
              making them more effective at reducing speeds along the entire corridor.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="safety-card">
            <h3>M65 Speed Cameras</h3>
            <span class="safety-location">M65 eastbound, multiple locations</span>
            <p>
              Fixed and variable speed cameras installed as part of the 2004 &pound;84M safety programme.
              Despite this, a series of fatal crashes in 2024 have prompted calls for a comprehensive
              safety review of the M65 between Junctions 5 and 14.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="safety-card">
            <h3>30mph Enforcement</h3>
            <span class="safety-location">A679 Hapton, residential areas</span>
            <p>
              Speed enforcement operates on the 30mph section of the A679 at Hapton.
              Community Speedwatch schemes are active in several Burnley wards.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="safety-card">
            <h3>Centenary Way Junction</h3>
            <span class="safety-location">Yorkshire Street / Church Street</span>
            <p>
              The old roundabout has been replaced with a signalised junction as part of Town2Turf.
              New pedestrian crossings installed. The pedestrian subway has been permanently closed
              and landscaped, with surface-level crossings replacing it.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
